content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 441.210 - Neonatal intensive care unit

State Regulations
A special unit, approved by the State, set up for the
treatment of infants from hour of birth through first 28 days; also of infants
up to three months of age with medical and surgical problems which are best
managed in a neonatal intensive care unit. Notes
